The paper proposes a methodology for automatically detecting the swim bladder in fish embryo images using image processing techniques and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, since the study involves the use of fish embryo models for toxicity assessment, it may also be relevant to the bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category.
